},"linkedAccounts":{"__ref":"LinkedAccounts:eb4faf0972a"},"isSuspended":false,"customDomainState":{"__typename":"CustomDomainState","live":{"__typename":"CustomDomain","domain":"blog.karoko.dev"}},"hasSubdomain":false,"verifications":{"__typename":"VerifiedInfo","isBookAuthor":false},"imageId":"1*dPQIqCCb9UtLpEl0-S7z_g.jpeg","socialStats":{"__typename":"SocialStats","followerCount":26,"followingCount":9,"collectionFollowingCount":0},"bio":"I write code in GO and I believe in collaboration to build successful products, extraordinary experiences, and lasting value for clients.","membership":{"__ref":"Membership:3ab211be-f72d-473c-8d27-7c31309bbbd7"},"allowNotes":true,"viewerEdge":{"__ref":"UserViewerEdge:userId:eb4faf0972a-viewerId:lo_413d4304e393"},"twitterScreenName":""},"Membership:3ab211be-f72d-473c-8d27-7c31309bbbd7":{"__typename":"Membership","tier":"MEMBER","id":"3ab211be-f72d-473c-8d27-7c31309bbbd7"},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_0":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_0","name":"6c9a","type":"H3","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Processing 1 Million Transactions in Under a Second Using Go — Part 1","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"ImageMetadata:1*0myhgmQjyYoHs9eUzOjijQ.png":{"__typename":"ImageMetadata","id":"1*0myhgmQjyYoHs9eUzOjijQ.png","originalHeight":1024,"originalWidth":1536,"focusPercentX":null,"focusPercentY":null,"alt":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_1":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_1","name":"b2bb","type":"IMG","href":null,"layout":"INSET_CENTER","metadata":{"__ref":"ImageMetadata:1*0myhgmQjyYoHs9eUzOjijQ.png"},"text":"Processing 1 millions transactions in under a second using GO.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_2":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_2","name":"7f2c","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"It’s Black Friday. Millions of shoppers are flooding an e-commerce platform, buying everything from 75-inch TVs to phone chargers they’ll lose in a week. Meanwhile, somewhere in a dimly lit office, an analytics team is frantically refreshing dashboards, waiting for insights that never seem to arrive.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_3":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_3","name":"c527","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"What if we could process 1 million transactions in under a second? Not with a cluster of GPUs or Kafka streams. Just Go.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_4":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_4","name":"5937","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"We’ll start with the simplest possible solution, watch it fail badly, then work through exactly why it fails and how to fix it. By the end, you’ll have a clear mental model of Go’s concurrency model, batch processing, worker pools, and what actually moves the needle on performance.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_5":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_5","name":"644a","type":"H3","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"The Challenge","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_6":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_6","name":"7ee9","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"We want to build a transaction processing system that handles massive volumes of e-commerce data quickly. Each transaction looks like this:","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_7":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_7","name":"820c","type":"PRE","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"{\n  \"order_id\": \"order_12345\",\n  \"user_id\": \"user_789\",\n  \"product_id\": \"laptop_pro_256\",\n  \"quantity\": 2,\n  \"price\": 1299.99,\n  \"timestamp\": \"2024-10-21T15:04:05Z\"\n}","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":{"__typename":"CodeBlockMetadata","mode":"AUTO","lang":"json"},"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_8":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_8","name":"d23e","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"The goal: process 1 million of these in under a second while tracking analytics like user spending totals and order volumes. No GPU cluster, no message queue. Just a single Go process.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[{"__typename":"Markup","type":"STRONG","start":0,"end":8,"href":null,"anchorType":null,"userId":null,"linkMetadata":null}],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_9":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_9","name":"d2da","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"That’s the bar. Let’s see how far the naive approach gets us.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_10":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_10","name":"c269","type":"BQ","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"A note on benchmarks: TPS figures throughout this article were measured on a MacBook Pro M2 Pro against a local PostgreSQL instance. Your numbers will differ depending on hardware and database setup. What matters is the relative improvement between approaches, not the exact number.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_11":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_11","name":"a587","type":"H3","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"The Naive Approach","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_12":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_12","name":"67ad","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Let’s start with the most obvious solution: read the file line by line and write each transaction to the database.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_13":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_13","name":"4854","type":"PRE","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"func processTransactions(filename string) error {\n    file, err := os.Open(filename)\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    defer file.Close()\n\n    scanner := bufio.NewScanner(file)\n    for scanner.Scan() {\n        var tx Transaction\n        if err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(scanner.Text()), &tx); err != nil {\n            continue\n        }\n        updateDatabase(tx)\n    }\n    return scanner.Err()\n}","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":{"__typename":"CodeBlockMetadata","mode":"AUTO","lang":"go"},"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_14":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_14","name":"5699","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Simple, readable, and correct. Let’s run it on 1 million records.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_15":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_15","name":"53fe","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Result: ~350 TPS.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[{"__typename":"Markup","type":"STRONG","start":0,"end":17,"href":null,"anchorType":null,"userId":null,"linkMetadata":null}],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_16":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_16","name":"a88d","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"At that rate, 1 million records takes roughly 47 minutes. We needed 0.5 seconds. We’re only off by a factor of 5,704. No big deal! 😅","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"MediaResource:6d9ebe77c87b4af608429a2fc971979e":{"__typename":"MediaResource","id":"6d9ebe77c87b4af608429a2fc971979e","iframeSrc":"https:\u002F\u002Fcdn.embedly.com\u002Fwidgets\u002Fmedia.html?src=https%3A%2F%2Fgiphy.com%2Fembed%2FYRPBhd3vscg5Fxx1DQ%2Ftwitter%2Fiframe&display_name=Giphy&url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia.giphy.com%2Fmedia%2Fv1.Y2lkPTc5MGI3NjExaHlkc3djbTRvYTh1OTQwcnl2NmcwMDdkNmJrczdvZjl4MWJxODhveiZlcD12MV9naWZzX3NlYXJjaCZjdD1n%2FYRPBhd3vscg5Fxx1DQ%2Fgiphy.gif&image=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia4.giphy.com%2Fmedia%2Fv1.Y2lkPTc5MGI3NjExOWV2ZjNuaXBvZ294M2kxNmViOXp3YzdqOTR0YmhjZGpoYWM2MTNmayZlcD12MV9pbnRlcm5hbF9naWZfYnlfaWQmY3Q9Zw%2FYRPBhd3vscg5Fxx1DQ%2Fgiphy_s.gif&type=text%2Fhtml&schema=giphy","iframeHeight":244,"iframeWidth":435,"title":"Pedro Pascal Laughing GIF by Crafture - Find & Share on GIPHY"},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_17":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_17","name":"68dd","type":"IFRAME","href":null,"layout":"INSET_CENTER","metadata":null,"text":"","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":{"__typename":"Iframe","mediaResource":{"__ref":"MediaResource:6d9ebe77c87b4af608429a2fc971979e"}},"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_18":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_18","name":"8411","type":"H3","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Why It’s So Slow","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_19":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_19","name":"1727","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Four things are working against us:","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_20":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_20","name":"589c","type":"OLI","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Single-threaded processing. We’re using one core on a machine that likely has several sitting idle.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[{"__typename":"Markup","type":"STRONG","start":0,"end":27,"href":null,"anchorType":null,"userId":null,"linkMetadata":null}],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_21":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_21","name":"dd23","type":"OLI","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"A million individual database calls. Each one has query overhead, network round trips, and execution cost.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[{"__typename":"Markup","type":"STRONG","start":0,"end":36,"href":null,"anchorType":null,"userId":null,"linkMetadata":null}],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_22":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_22","name":"2055","type":"OLI","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"No batching. Every transaction is treated as a separate unit of work.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[{"__typename":"Markup","type":"STRONG","start":0,"end":12,"href":null,"anchorType":null,"userId":null,"linkMetadata":null}],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_23":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_23","name":"49a0","type":"OLI","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Sequential I\u002FO. We read a line, parse it, update analytics, write to the database, then repeat.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[{"__typename":"Markup","type":"STRONG","start":0,"end":15,"href":null,"anchorType":null,"userId":null,"linkMetadata":null}],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"ImageMetadata:1*3CXM5-w60IdvkKky1vp2ZA.png":{"__typename":"ImageMetadata","id":"1*3CXM5-w60IdvkKky1vp2ZA.png","originalHeight":660,"originalWidth":1472,"focusPercentX":null,"focusPercentY":null,"alt":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_24":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_24","name":"c965","type":"IMG","href":null,"layout":"INSET_CENTER","metadata":{"__ref":"ImageMetadata:1*3CXM5-w60IdvkKky1vp2ZA.png"},"text":"","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_25":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_25","name":"ebc8","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"The important thing to notice is that these are not all the same kind of bottleneck.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_26":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_26","name":"b441","type":"ULI","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"File reading and database writes are I\u002FO-bound.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_27":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_27","name":"75f1","type":"ULI","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"JSON parsing and in-memory aggregation are CPU-bound.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_28":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_28","name":"24dc","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Different bottlenecks respond to different fixes. Instead of trying to make one giant sequential loop faster, we need to separate the pipeline and optimize each stage on its own terms.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[{"__typename":"Markup","type":"EM","start":102,"end":108,"href":null,"anchorType":null,"userId":null,"linkMetadata":null}],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_29":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_29","name":"8872","type":"H3","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Decoupling Reading from Processing","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_30":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_30","name":"4ab0","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"The first improvement is to stop treating file reading and transaction processing as one sequential block.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_31":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_31","name":"9a5f","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"If we separate them with a channel, the file reader can continue feeding work while another goroutine consumes it.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_32":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_32","name":"5531","type":"PRE","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"func betterProcessing(filename string) error {\n    lines := make(chan string, 1000)\n\n    go func() {\n        file, err := os.Open(filename)\n        if err != nil {\n            close(lines)\n            return\n        }\n        defer file.Close()\n\n        scanner := bufio.NewScanner(file)\n        for scanner.Scan() {\n            lines \u003C- scanner.Text()\n        }\n        close(lines)\n    }()\n\n    for line := range lines {\n        var tx Transaction\n        if err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(line), &tx); err != nil {\n            continue\n        }\n        updateDatabase(tx)\n    }\n    return nil\n}","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":{"__typename":"CodeBlockMetadata","mode":"AUTO","lang":"go"},"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_33":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_33","name":"9e32","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Let’s test that.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_34":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_34","name":"ca22","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Result: ~400 TPS","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[{"__typename":"Markup","type":"STRONG","start":0,"end":16,"href":null,"anchorType":null,"userId":null,"linkMetadata":null}],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_35":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_35","name":"6d90","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"That’s better, but barely. The reader and processor now overlap, but we’re still hitting the database once per transaction. That’s still a million individual writes.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_36":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_36","name":"80c1","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Pipelining helps, but pipelining alone doesn’t solve the real bottleneck.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_37":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_37","name":"1509","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"A quick note on channel buffer size: too small and the producer stalls; too large and you retain more data in memory than necessary. In practice, a buffer somewhere around 1,000 to 10,000 is a reasonable starting point for this kind of workload.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_38":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_38","name":"1582","type":"H3","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Adding Multiple Workers","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_39":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_39","name":"130d","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"The channel version gave us pipeline parallelism, but we still have a single goroutine doing all the processing.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_40":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_40","name":"6c35","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"If we spawn multiple workers reading from the same channel, Go’s scheduler can spread that work across multiple CPU cores.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_41":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_41","name":"c27a","type":"PRE","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"func workerPoolVersion(filename string, workerCount int) error {\n    lines := make(chan string, 10000)\n    var wg sync.WaitGroup\n\n    for i := 0; i \u003C workerCount; i++ {\n        wg.Add(1)\n        go func() {\n            defer wg.Done()\n            for line := range lines {\n                var tx Transaction\n                if err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(line), &tx); err != nil {\n                    continue\n                }\n                updateDatabase(tx)\n            }\n        }()\n    }\n\n    go func() {\n        file, err := os.Open(filename)\n        if err != nil {\n            close(lines)\n            return\n        }\n        defer file.Close()\n\n        scanner := bufio.NewScanner(file)\n        for scanner.Scan() {\n            lines \u003C- scanner.Text()\n        }\n        close(lines)\n    }()\n\n    wg.Wait()\n    return nil\n}","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":{"__typename":"CodeBlockMetadata","mode":"AUTO","lang":"go"},"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_42":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_42","name":"95f4","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"With 8 workers:","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_43":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_43","name":"0f1d","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Result: ~1,700 TPS.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[{"__typename":"Markup","type":"STRONG","start":0,"end":19,"href":null,"anchorType":null,"userId":null,"linkMetadata":null}],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"ImageMetadata:1*E394XVz-aIDye3JqSYoxoA.png":{"__typename":"ImageMetadata","id":"1*E394XVz-aIDye3JqSYoxoA.png","originalHeight":710,"originalWidth":1472,"focusPercentX":null,"focusPercentY":null,"alt":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_44":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_44","name":"2219","type":"IMG","href":null,"layout":"INSET_CENTER","metadata":{"__ref":"ImageMetadata:1*E394XVz-aIDye3JqSYoxoA.png"},"text":"","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_45":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_45","name":"4c0f","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"That’s about a 5x improvement just from parallelism alone.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_46":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_46","name":"5b1a","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"But we’re still nowhere near the target, because the design still performs a database operation for every transaction. Multiple workers help parse faster, but they do not change the cost model of a million round trips.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_47":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_47","name":"63de","type":"H3","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Batching Database Writes","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_48":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_48","name":"f021","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Every database call has overhead: query parsing, transaction work, execution, network round trip. Even if a single insert is fast, doing it a million times is not.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_49":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_49","name":"57df","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"The next fix is to stop writing one row at a time. Instead, accumulate work in memory and flush it in batches.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_50":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_50","name":"baf4","type":"PRE","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"func batchProcessing(lines \u003C-chan string, batchSize int) error {\n    var batch []Transaction\n\n    for line := range lines {\n        var tx Transaction\n        if err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(line), &tx); err != nil {\n            continue\n        }\n\n        batch = append(batch, tx)\n\n        if len(batch) \u003E= batchSize {\n            if err := processBatch(batch); err != nil {\n                return err\n            }\n            batch = batch[:0] \u002F\u002F reset length, keep underlying array\n        }\n    }\n\n    if len(batch) \u003E 0 {\n        return processBatch(batch)\n    }\n\n    return nil\n}","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":{"__typename":"CodeBlockMetadata","mode":"AUTO","lang":"go"},"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_51":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_51","name":"520c","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"The batch = batch[:0] is worth calling out. It resets the slice length to zero while keeping the same underlying array, so the next batch can reuse the existing allocation instead of allocating fresh memory every time.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[{"__typename":"Markup","type":"CODE","start":4,"end":21,"href":null,"anchorType":null,"userId":null,"linkMetadata":null}],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_52":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_52","name":"364b","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Batch size is a tuning knob:","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_53":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_53","name":"d5f0","type":"ULI","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Too small and you still make too many database calls.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_54":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_54","name":"b85c","type":"ULI","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Too large and you hold more in memory than necessary, and failures affect larger chunks of work.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_55":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_55","name":"eb20","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"In practice, 500 to 1,000 is a good starting range. Benchmark it on your own machine instead of guessing.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_56":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_56","name":"3413","type":"H3","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Worker-Local Aggregation Beats Shared State","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_57":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_57","name":"3156","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"At this point we have multiple workers consuming transactions concurrently. The next question is where analytics state should live.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_58":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_58","name":"a729","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"A common first instinct is to put all per-user analytics in one shared map and protect it with a mutex. That is correct, but under load it turns shared state into a bottleneck.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_59":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_59","name":"fe32","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Even if you get fancier with per-user locks, you’re still paying synchronization cost in the hot path.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_60":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_60","name":"76f5","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"A better approach is to avoid shared-state contention during processing entirely.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_61":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_61","name":"30e2","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Instead of having every worker update one global analytics map, let each worker own its own private map.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_62":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_62","name":"8d43","type":"PRE","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"type UserAnalytics struct {\n UserID      string\n TotalOrders int\n TotalSpent  float64\n}\ntype Processor struct {\n workerMaps map[int]map[string]*UserAnalytics\n mu         sync.Mutex\n}","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":{"__typename":"CodeBlockMetadata","mode":"AUTO","lang":"go"},"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_63":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_63","name":"c6e6","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Each worker initializes its own local map and processes batches independently:","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_64":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_64","name":"ba48","type":"PRE","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"func (p *Processor) ProcessStream(id int, lines \u003C-chan string, batchSize int) error {\n p.mu.Lock()\n p.workerMaps[id] = make(map[string]*UserAnalytics)\n p.mu.Unlock()\n\n var batch []Transaction\n\n for line := range lines {\n  var tx Transaction\n  if err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(line), &tx); err != nil {\n   continue\n  }\n\n  batch = append(batch, tx)\n\n  if len(batch) \u003E= batchSize {\n   p.applyTransactions(id, batch)\n   batch = batch[:0]\n  }\n }\n\n if len(batch) \u003E 0 {\n  p.applyTransactions(id, batch)\n }\n\n return nil\n}","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":{"__typename":"CodeBlockMetadata","mode":"AUTO","lang":"go"},"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_65":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_65","name":"011d","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"And the per-batch aggregation is straightforward:","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_66":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_66","name":"9169","type":"PRE","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"func(p * Processor) applyTransactions(workerID int, txs[] Transaction) {\n    localMap: = p.workerMaps[workerID]\n\n    for _,\n    tx: = range txs {\n        ua, ok: = localMap[tx.UserID]\n        if !ok {\n            ua = & UserAnalytics {\n                UserID: tx.UserID\n            }\n            localMap[tx.UserID] = ua\n        }\n\n        ua.TotalOrders++\n            ua.TotalSpent += tx.Price * float64(tx.Quantity)\n    }\n}","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":{"__typename":"CodeBlockMetadata","mode":"AUTO","lang":"go"},"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_67":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_67","name":"17bb","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"The key property here is that each worker only touches its own map. No other worker reads or writes that data while processing is happening, so there is zero lock contention in the hot path.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[{"__typename":"Markup","type":"STRONG","start":153,"end":189,"href":null,"anchorType":null,"userId":null,"linkMetadata":null}],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_68":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_68","name":"6c64","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"When processing is done, we merge the worker-local maps into one final snapshot:","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_69":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_69","name":"9634","type":"PRE","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"func (p *Processor) Snapshot() map[string]*UserAnalytics {\n      merged := make(map[string]*UserAnalytics)\n\n      for _, workerMap := range p.workerMaps {\n          for userID, ua := range workerMap {\n              if existing, ok := merged[userID]; ok {\n                  existing.TotalOrders += ua.TotalOrders\n                  existing.TotalSpent += ua.TotalSpent\n              } else {\n                  merged[userID] = &UserAnalytics{\n                      UserID:      ua.UserID,\n                      TotalOrders: ua.TotalOrders,\n                      TotalSpent:  ua.TotalSpent,\n                  }\n              }\n          }\n      }\n\n      return merged\n}","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":{"__typename":"CodeBlockMetadata","mode":"AUTO","lang":"go"},"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_70":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_70","name":"8d77","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"This is the real concurrency win.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_71":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_71","name":"a67c","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Instead of making every transaction fight over shared memory, we let workers run independently and pay the coordination cost once at the end.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_72":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_72","name":"3742","type":"H3","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Putting It All Together","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_73":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_73","name":"3100","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"With all the pieces combined, the final pipeline looks like this:","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_74":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_74","name":"0df3","type":"OLI","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"One goroutine reads the NDJSON file line by line.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_75":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_75","name":"b8fe","type":"OLI","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Lines are pushed into a buffered channel.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_76":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_76","name":"7e96","type":"OLI","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"A worker pool parses transactions concurrently.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_77":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_77","name":"366e","type":"OLI","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Each worker batches transactions and updates its own private analytics map.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_78":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_78","name":"faa2","type":"OLI","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"When processing completes, the worker-local maps are merged.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_79":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_79","name":"f4ae","type":"OLI","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"The final aggregated result is flushed to PostgreSQL in bulk.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_80":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_80","name":"9abb","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"That architecture matters because it keeps the hot path almost entirely in memory:","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_81":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_81","name":"b362","type":"ULI","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"file reading is cheap and sequential","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_82":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_82","name":"e6c7","type":"ULI","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"parsing is spread across multiple cores","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_83":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_83","name":"89af","type":"ULI","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"analytics updates happen without shared-state contention","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_84":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_84","name":"d31e","type":"ULI","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"the database is touched once at the end instead of once per transaction","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_85":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_85","name":"b734","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"That last point is the biggest one. The main performance gain is not “using goroutines.” It’s moving database writes off the hot path and replacing a million small writes with a single bulk flush.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[{"__typename":"Markup","type":"EM","start":70,"end":87,"href":null,"anchorType":null,"userId":null,"linkMetadata":null}],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"ImageMetadata:1*5uF9clg8eGfm9rSt4pNw5w.png":{"__typename":"ImageMetadata","id":"1*5uF9clg8eGfm9rSt4pNw5w.png","originalHeight":887,"originalWidth":1774,"focusPercentX":null,"focusPercentY":null,"alt":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_86":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_86","name":"1aa6","type":"IMG","href":null,"layout":"INSET_CENTER","metadata":{"__ref":"ImageMetadata:1*5uF9clg8eGfm9rSt4pNw5w.png"},"text":"The final pipeline","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_87":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_87","name":"c984","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Here’s how the configurations compare on 1 million transactions:","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"ImageMetadata:1*co4oVHpaNOwMJD0FbtQiDg.png":{"__typename":"ImageMetadata","id":"1*co4oVHpaNOwMJD0FbtQiDg.png","originalHeight":195,"originalWidth":829,"focusPercentX":null,"focusPercentY":null,"alt":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_88":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_88","name":"5dea","type":"IMG","href":null,"layout":"INSET_CENTER","metadata":{"__ref":"ImageMetadata:1*co4oVHpaNOwMJD0FbtQiDg.png"},"text":"Configuration comparison for 1 million transactions: 10 workers and a batch size of 500 performed best on my machine.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_89":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_89","name":"c33c","type":"BQ","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"These numbers were measured on a MacBook Pro M2 Pro. Your results will vary based on hardware, storage, and database setup. The relative behavior matters more than the exact number.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_90":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_90","name":"0d3a","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"The default configuration is the sweet spot on my machine. Pushing the worker count higher doesn’t necessarily help. Past a certain point, scheduler overhead, memory traffic, and coordination cost outweigh the gains from more parallelism.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_91":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_91","name":"2097","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Concurrency helps, but only when the architecture gives each worker useful independent work to do.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_92":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_92","name":"bee6","type":"H3","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"What’s in Part 2","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_93":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_93","name":"c0ea","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"This was the proof of concept. We now know the core processing model works:","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_94":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_94","name":"ba3a","type":"ULI","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"stream NDJSON instead of loading everything into memory","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_95":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_95","name":"e941","type":"ULI","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"spread parsing across a worker pool","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_96":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_96","name":"39ef","type":"ULI","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"aggregate in worker-local maps to avoid lock contention","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_97":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_97","name":"0d28","type":"ULI","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"bulk flush the final result to PostgreSQL","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_98":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_98","name":"1573","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"In Part 2, we’ll take that fast core and wrap it in a cleaner application structure: configuration, migrations, a repository layer, a service layer, Redis-backed reads, and an HTTP API for querying analytics.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[{"__typename":"Markup","type":"A","start":3,"end":9,"href":"https:\u002F\u002Fmedium.com\u002F@kennedykaroko\u002Fprocessing-1-million-transactions-in-under-a-second-using-go-part-2-c075800fe7a4","anchorType":"LINK","userId":null,"linkMetadata":null}],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:0b0d012abef1_99":{"__typename":"Paragraph","id":"0b0d012abef1_99","name":"9786","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"The complete implementation is already on GitHub if you want to compare the proof of concept to the more structured version.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[{"__typename":"Markup","type":"A","start":42,"end":48,"href":"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fiamkaroko\u002Ftx-processor","anchorType":"LINK","userId":null,"linkMetadata":null}],"codeBlockMetadata":null,"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"MediaResource:caf371552b77d2d6e37ad31389d5b79b":{"__typename":"MediaResource","id":"caf371552b77d2d6e37ad31389d5b79b","iframeSrc":"https:\u002F\u002Fcdn.embedly.com\u002Fwidgets\u002Fmedia.html?src=https%3A%2F%2Fgiphy.com%2Fembed%2FL83H4eHwEVChg2Y6QH%2Ftwitter%2Fiframe&display_name=Giphy&url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia.giphy.com%2Fmedia%2Fv1.Y2lkPTc5MGI3NjExenV4b29iaXdoMjB0N2pncmd3amhtMnphMHdiYWI1NXd4bmtxa2dxNSZlcD12MV9naWZzX3NlYXJjaCZjdD1n%2FL83H4eHwEVChg2Y6QH%2Fgiphy.gif&image=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia3.giphy.com%2Fmedia%2Fv1.Y2lkPTc5MGI3NjExMGJsejZ5M3NvZ2E4cXk1aHN5cmYxZGdhOTdvbjN2OWVnY2Z5bmd4dyZlcD12MV9pbnRlcm5hbF9naWZfYnlfaWQmY3Q9Zw%2FL83H4eHwEVChg2Y6QH%2Fgiphy_s.gif&type=text%2Fhtml&schema=giphy","iframeHeight":43